  "name": "A76: launch a viable spaceship and win the space victory on arrival",
  "notes": "3x3 grassland, two civs each with one city (neither is eliminable). p1's city c1 holds the Apollo Program (the derived gate) and p1 owns a minimum-viable ship (7 structural + 1 each of propulsion/fuel/habitation/lifeSupport/solar). Year -4000 uses 50-year steps, so the ship's 31 flight-years compress to a 1-turn arrival (idiv(31,50)=0 -> max(1,0)=1). launchShip sets launched+arrivalTurn; two endTurns wrap the game turn to the arrival turn, processSpace fires the space victory BEFORE checkGameEnd. Result: gameOver, winner p1, victory 'space'. Break launch viability, the Apollo gate, or the arrival math in either engine and the final hash moves -> this pin fails the instant A76 regresses. Civ1-authentic gate; the flight-time model is original (rules.ssFlight, sim-runner-swept).",
